# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Proprietary kernel library — never publish.
#
# Forge is the open-core compiler. The industries/ kernel library
# is the proprietary product. This rule is a safety net: the
# repo is PRIVATE today, so existing tracked files under
# industries/ stay tracked (gitignore only blocks NEW untracked
# files). When the forge repo flips public, every kernel file
# already on disk will be invisible to git unless explicitly
# force-added, and new contributors won't accidentally stage
# proprietary content.
#
# To add a new industry kernel deliberately while the rule is in
# place, use:  git add -f industries/<vertical>/<file>.eml
#
# Generated artifacts from `--target all` runs land under
# industries/<vertical>/build/ — never commit these. They are
# reproducible from source and bloat history.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
industries/
industries/**/build/
